  "text": "The async runtime waker mechanism in rust-lang/rust's standard library spans 4 key files:\n\n1. **`library/core/src/task/wake.rs`** \u2014 The central file. Defines `RawWaker` (data pointer + vtable reference), `RawWakerVTable` (the virtual function pointer table with clone/wake/wake_by_ref/drop), `Waker` (the safe wrapper that calls through the vtable), `LocalWaker` (non-Send variant), `Context` (carries the Waker into poll), and `ContextBuilder`.\n\n2. **`library/core/src/task/poll.rs`** \u2014 Defines `Poll<T>` enum (`Ready(T)` / `Pending`) which is the return type of the future polling loop.\n\n3. **`library/core/src/future/future.rs`** \u2014 Defines the `Future` trait with its `fn poll(self: Pin<&mut Self>, cx: &mut Context<'_>) -> Poll<Self::Output>` method, which is the polling loop entry point that receives the waker via Context.\n\n4. **`library/alloc/src/task.rs`** \u2014 Defines the safe `Wake` trait (and `LocalWake`) that provides a higher-level, Arc-based alternative to manually constructing `RawWaker` vtables. Contains `From<Arc<W>> for Waker` implementations that bridge the safe trait to the raw vtable mechanism.",
